Citation.sTitle: Solubilities of 1-Hexyl-3-methylimidazole Nitrate and 1-Octyl-3-methylimidazole Nitrate in Selected Solvents
Citation.sAbstract: Solubilities of two ionic liquids, 1-hexyl-3-methylimidazolium nitrate ([HMIM][NO3]) and 1-octyl-3-methylimidazolium nitrate ([OMIM][NO3]), in 10 organic solvents (n-pentane, n-hexane, cyclohexane, n-heptane, n-octane, benzene, toluene, o-xylene, p-xylene, and m-xylene) were measured in the range between (278.15 and 343.15) K using a static analytical gravimetric method, respectively. The logarithm of the mole fraction solubilities of these two ILs in the 10 selected solvents was correlated by a linear function of inversed temperatures.
